definition: enough (sufficient)/enough (too much)/(coll.) (before adj.) really/(coll.) to reach by stretching out

sentences.english: Is this image fresh enough to have an effect?
sentences.chinese: 这个形象的新鲜度够不够产生效果？

sentences.english: If flexibility isn’t your strong suit, simply bend your knees to adjust.
sentences.chinese: 如果你的躯体不够灵活，可以弯曲膝部来调整一下。

sentences.english: Because I diden't have enough, but now I do. the little boy replied.
sentences.chinese: 因为我之前不够，但我现在已经够了，小孩回答。

sentences.english: He seemed to have no desire to go there; besides, his clothes were not good enough.
sentences.chinese: 他似乎不想去那儿，再加他的衣服也不够体面。
这些够不够具有威胁性？

sentences.english: The knife didn't cut deep enough.
But tempering alone is usually not enough.
sentences.chinese: 但是单纯的退火是不够的。

sentences.english: His main complaint was that, at just three lanes, the M25 was not big or bold enough.
sentences.chinese: 他那时还抱怨说M25公路只有三车道，不够宽。

sentences.english: If no returns, one-inch the hole.
sentences.chinese: 如果返高不够，开1英寸的小孔。

sentences.english: I very much want to buy the English dictionary, but unfortunately Idon't have enough money on me.
sentences.chinese: 我很想买这本英书契典，遗憾的是我身上带的钱不够。

sentences.english: And it's not enough to just depend on books in the proccess of learning.
sentences.chinese: 对于其学习过程仅仅依靠书本及培训是远远不够的。

sentences.english: 'Protestations' that the company isn't affiliated with the Chinese military aren't enough, he said.
sentences.chinese: 仅仅郑重声明公司和中国军方没有联系还不够。

sentences.english: He says this will help the industry, but not enough.
sentences.chinese: 他说，油价下降对航空业有好处，但这并不够。

sentences.english: I could never thank you enough.
Willing is not enough , we must do.
sentences.chinese: 光是希望是不够的，非去做不可。

definition: enough (sufficient)/enough (too much)/(coll.) (before adj.) really/(coll.) to reach by stretching out
like that/in that way/or so/so/so very much/about/in that case
won't do/be out of the question/be no good/not work/not be capable
